Not discrediting the heroic actions of the people involved, but essentially the guys rushed someone with a box cutter; the rifle jammed and the pistol was only used on the first guy, so in all it sounds like one shot was fired.  I know they didn't KNOW the rifle would jam but how do you convey drama on the screen? text: As Hollywood Tries to Stop New Patriotic Movie, Clint Eastwood Gives Them Brutal Surprise         Clint Eastwood‚Äôs new movie, ‚ÄúThe 15:17 to Paris,‚Äù is based on true events, where three American heroes stopped a terrorist on a Paris train in 2015, and it is causing the Hollywood crowd to go nuts.  They just tried to put the kibosh on certain scenes that didn‚Äôt fit their liberal agenda, and boy, that made Eastwood mad.  So, the famous actor and director who voted for President Donald Trump just slapped the leftists hard with a brutal surprise.  You‚Äôre going to love it.     Clint Eastwood is an American icon and is probably the most famous conservative actor and director in Hollywood.  Eastwood‚Äôs legendary work affords him the ability to pick and chose what type of movies he‚Äôll make, and he loves making patriotic American movies.     His current film, ‚ÄúThe 15:17 to Paris,‚Äù is in the final edits, but the Hollywood crowd hates it, and they tried to stop certain people from seeing it.  The reason is the pro-American message it sends, described in this synopsis on Google:  ‚ÄúIn the early evening of August 21, 2015, the world watched in stunned silence as the media reported a thwarted terrorist attack on Thalys train #9364 bound for Paris‚Äîan attempt prevented by three courageous young Americans traveling through Europe.‚Äù     The summary adds, ‚ÄúThroughout the harrowing ordeal, their friendship never wavers, making it their greatest weapon and allowing them to save the lives of the more than 500 passengers on board.  The heroic trio is comprised of Anthony Sadler, Oregon National Guardsman Alek Skarlatos, and U.S. Air Force Airman First Class Spencer Stone, who play themselves in the film.‚Äù     The movie stirs real patriotic emotion and honors the three American heroes who have military backgrounds.  It shows an Islamic terrorist, who gains entry into France as a migrant, attempting to slaughter 500 people, with three Americans stopping him.  This just isn‚Äôt the type of movie the Hollywood crowd makes, and they tried to screw Eastwood by giving it an ‚ÄúR‚Äù rating.     The reason they gave for the ‚ÄúR‚Äù rating was it showed ‚Äúviolence,‚Äù and this pissed off Clint Eastwood, who is making this film so teens could also see a movie with real American values.  It was a cheap shot by the liberal Hollywood idiots, and Eastwood decided that wasn‚Äôt going to happen.  The legendary star shocked the Hollywood crowd by taking on the rating board himself, something that never happens.  And, not only did he take them on, he blew them away.     ‚ÄúClint Eastwood has won an appeal to overturn the R rating originally assigned to his upcoming film, The 15:17 to Paris.  Instead, it will be rated PG-13.  According to a source, the R rating was given for the train attack scene at the center of the film, which the Classification and Rating Administration described as ‚Äòa sequence of violence and bloody images,‚Äô‚Äù reported Hollywood Reporter.     They added, ‚ÄúThe Classification and Rating Appeals Board says it reviews 800 to 900 films each year, with fewer than 12 ratings a year appealed.  Eastwood represented his own film on behalf of Warner Bros., which opens the film in theaters on Feb. 9.‚Äù     Clint doesn‚Äôt just play a ‚Äútough guy‚Äù in his movies, he showed those Hollywood snakes that he really is a tough guy who won‚Äôt be pushed around.  He‚Äôll make any darn movie he wants to make, and they won‚Äôt stop him from making sure as many Americans as possible can see it.     Here‚Äôs the highly awaited trailer for ‚ÄúThe 15:17 to Paris‚Äù that just came out:       click here:   https://www.youtube.co m/watch?v=IC_lnyn2R2Q     In case you‚Äôre wondering how much the Hollywood crowd detests this movie for its pro-American military theme along with its anti-Islam, anti-migrant message, here‚Äôs how one Hollywood critic describes it:     But in the hands of someone like Eastwood, this [movie] reads like a recruitment ad for the military.  Nothing diminishes the heroism of these three men, but in Eastwood‚Äôs hands, it looks like he‚Äôs coasting on their achievements to tell a story that will make some people think that they too can be heroes if they just head down to their local recruitment office.  [Source: Collider]     Well, let the haters hate.  They loathe patriotism and they despise middle-class working Americans who love this country.  They can‚Äôt stand Clint Eastwood who said that former President Barack Obama is ‚Äúthe greatest hoax ever perpetrated on the American people.‚Äù     Lastly, what in the hell is wrong with sending the message to teens that they too can be heroes?  What is wrong with giving some kids the idea that joining the military is a heroic thing to do?  This is exactly the kind of movie our young people need to see in today‚Äôs world that is filled with idiot celebrities pushing anti-American messages.  If this movie inspires just one young American to join the military and make their life worthwhile, then Clint Eastwood‚Äôs film will be a resounding success.     http://us-daily.tk/hollywood-t ries-stop-new-patriotic-movie- clint-eastwood-gives-brutal- surprise

This is the first movie screening in years that I walked out of feeling like I just finished re-education and nothing else. I don't know what Eastwood was thinking. It's so heavy handed, yet manages to be nothing at all. The title characters actually do quite well, it's clear they received excellent direction. It actually takes away from the story of these men, turns them into action heroes rather than ordinary people tasked with doing extraordinary things. Someone should have pulled the plug. Easily the worst movie Clint Eastwood has made in decades

They were not the smartest nor the best students growing up, but they had loving, Christian mothers who formed their inner cores. text: It's sad this is getting reamed by biased "critics" with an ax to grind. Too bad it doesn't feature the appropriate narrative, like a certain ironically pro-ethnostate, pro-wall, pro-nationalism movie. Too bad it's directed by an undesirable. Too bad it portrays Christianity in a positive light. Too bad it portrays a real-life black hero that helped saved hundreds of lives; I guess he's not Woke-kanda enough.   The movie was pretty good given the artistic direction Heston went with. No, the acting from the three leads isn't good. It's not supposed to be. They're not actors. Complaining about this is like complaining about an indie art house movie that's black and white and silent; that's the point of the movie, not a weakness. It's a very unique piece of art; instead of the heroes telling us their story, they show it to us. It's amazing how they acted out their lives up to that point, and re-lived that moment.   Props to Jenna Fisher, Tony Hale, Jaleel White, Judy Greer, and many others for having the courage to act in a movie Hollywood will despise.

text: I saw this movie at the $2.50 last night, the reviews weren't favorable (unusual for a movie directed by Clint Eastwood) and it ended up in the "cheap" theater not long after it played in the 1st run theaters. It wasn't a long movie, about 90 minutes, but I thought it was a decent movie. I remember hearing about the incident but was a little fuzzy on details, so I was glad to see the action as it really happened. I think perhaps one of the reasons for the low box-office/reviews is that there is a slight religious undertone to the story--and that can turn a lot of people off. Many years ago that wouldn't have been an issue in Hollywood, but it is now. That's just my opinion. Anyway, I don't feel as though I wasted my money.
